author: Matthew Medsger
title: Bay State’s election chief concerned about election denial, money in politics
description: Secretary of the Commonwealth Bill Galvin said that he and other state election officials have shared concerns over emerging technology -- like deep fakes and AI -- and over the increasing number of voters and politicians who are calling the legitimacy of elections into question.

title: As police increasingly use facial recognition technology, calls grow for regulations
description: Legal and AI experts are calling on the federal government to set national standards as some police services use facial recognition technology to help solve crimes.

author: Sarah Brookes
title: Going under: The flood-prone Perth suburbs at risk of being uninsurable
description: There are some communities that modern technology and science now suggest, with the benefit of hindsight and projections, it might have been wiser not to build.
